data.description: Welcome home to 237 Holly Drive, an exceptional colonial in a quiet neighborhood located in the highly regarded Central Bucks School District.  This beautiful (the pictures tell the story!) 4 Bedroom, 2 1/2 Bath home, with 2774 square feet of living space has been well maintained: 2012 - Propane Furnace; Air Conditioner; 2013 - New Windows; Propane Fireplace; Sump Pump Water Back-up; Fireplace Facing; 2017 - Vinyl Siding; 2019 - Tankless Water Heater.   Note: Sellers Disclosure has been updated and a Home Inspection Report is available; both are included in Documents.  Radon and Termite reports are expected by Tuesday and will be included once available.  The outdoor space includes a large deck designed for entertaining or quiet relaxation and a classic shed that compliments this great home.  Conveniently located near Township Parks, Lake Galena, Doylestown Borough, Great Shopping (Wegmans, Costco, Airport Square) and Restaurants, Routes 202, 309 and SEPTA Trains.  New Hope is a half hour away!  Public Records indicate that this property has 3 bedrooms and that there is $960,000 owed on the mortgage; both are incorrect.  237 Holly Drive has 4 bedrooms and $151,941 is owed on the mortgage.  Both of these issues have been reported to Bright.  Bright hasn't provided any feedback regarding when this misinformation will be resolved.  The listing will be updated once Bright completes the review.    Also, note that the deck has been repaired recently.  The new pressure-treated boards have not been painted; the contractor indicated that the painting should occur in late winter, early spring.
